<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,669,2028]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,669,695]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This distinctive species (
<figureCitation box="[567,709,669,695]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–28" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[176,1412,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-32@14.[176,1412,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 18–28. Habitus images of Cyrtocapsus spp. 18, 19, C. discalis, holotype male. 18, dorsal aspect. 19, lateral aspect. 20–22, C. elutipes. 20, male, dorsal aspect. 21, female, dorsal aspect. 22, female, lateral aspect. 23, 24, C. femoralis, lectotype male. 23, dorsal aspect. 24, lateral aspect. 25, 26, C. fiuzai. 25, male, dorsal aspect. 26, female, dorsal aspect. 27, 28, C. glabratus, holotype male. 27, dorsal aspect. 28, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646371" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646371/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 23, 24</figureCitation>
), misidentified by all authors since its original description (see discussion under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergroth" authorityYear="1910" box="[351,473,705,732]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Miccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elutipes">
<emphasis box="[351,473,705,732]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. elutipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), is distinguished by the dark brown dorsum with the embolium and apical area of the corium pale brown or brownish orange, and the mostly dark brown femora with only the bases of the front and middle femora and the basal half of the hind femur pale, and the basal fourth of all tibiae dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,669,2028]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
It is similar in general body color to 
<taxonomicName box="[621,717,813,840]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fiuzai">
<emphasis box="[621,717,813,840]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. fiuzai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[735,874,813,840]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–28" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[176,1412,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-32@14.[176,1412,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 18–28. Habitus images of Cyrtocapsus spp. 18, 19, C. discalis, holotype male. 18, dorsal aspect. 19, lateral aspect. 20–22, C. elutipes. 20, male, dorsal aspect. 21, female, dorsal aspect. 22, female, lateral aspect. 23, 24, C. femoralis, lectotype male. 23, dorsal aspect. 24, lateral aspect. 25, 26, C. fiuzai. 25, male, dorsal aspect. 26, female, dorsal aspect. 27, 28, C. glabratus, holotype male. 27, dorsal aspect. 28, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646371" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646371/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 25, 26</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1909" box="[896,1062,813,840]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[896,1062,813,840]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1080,1165,813,839]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–39" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,181,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-16@27.[170,1418,181,1883]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 29–39. Habitus images of Cyrtocapsus spp. 29, 30, C. grenadensis. 29, male, dorsal aspect. 30, female, dorsal aspect. 31, C. guianus, holotype female, dorsal aspect. 32, 33, C. haitianus. 32, male dorsal aspect. 33, female, dorsal aspect. 34, C. intermedius, female, dorsal aspect. 35, 36, C. lazelli. 35, male, dorsal aspect. 36, female, dorsal aspect. 37, 38, C. marginatus. 37, lectotype male, dorsal aspect. 38, paralectotype female, dorsal aspect. 39, C. mesoamericanus, holotype male, dorsal aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646373/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName box="[1235,1436,813,840]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metafemoratus">
<emphasis box="[1235,1436,813,840]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. metafemoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,300,849,875]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–48" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-16@31.[170,1418,181,1883]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 40–48. Habitus images of Cyrtocapsus spp. 40, 41, C. metafemoratus. 40, male, dorsal aspect. 41, holotype female, dorsal aspect. 42, 43, C. nordestinus. 42, male, dorsal aspect. 43, male, lateral aspect. 44, 45, C. pallipes. 44, male, dorsal aspect. 45, female, dorsal aspect. 46, 47, C. paraensis, holotype female (of C. bolivianus). 46, dorsal aspect. 47, lateral aspect. 48, C. paraguaiensis, holotype female, dorsal aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646375/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 40, 41</figureCitation>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[494,591,849,876]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fiuzai">
<emphasis box="[494,591,849,876]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. fiuzai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1909" box="[650,817,849,876]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[650,817,849,876]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having all the femora apically fuscous (rather than uniformly pale) and the different parameres. It most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[967,1168,885,912]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metafemoratus">
<emphasis box="[967,1168,885,912]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">C. metafemoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the latter differs in having only the hind femur darkened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
